cff-version: 1.2.0
message: If you use this work, please cite it using the metadata below.
type: dataset
title: Network Performance Measurement and Analysis Experiment
abstract: This dataset comprises the results of an experiment designed to characterize
  network performance characteristics under controlled conditions. The research involved
  configuring multiple compute nodes (rapla, tapa, valga) with specific network topologies
  utilizing Time-Based Flow Control and NetEm emulation for latency manipulation.
  Scripts were executed to establish secure remote access via SSH key configuration,
  install dependencies, and generate synthetic data streams. Measurements included
  interface configurations, routing tables, QoS parameters, and energy consumption
  metrics captured during synchronized client-server interactions. The experiment
  generated multiple iterations of network traffic simulation and data transfer processes,
  culminating in the creation of pcapng files for detailed analysis.
